## 🚀 GitHub Pages Deployment

### Phase 1: GitHub Account (2 minutes)

- [ ] Have GitHub account (create at github.com if needed)
- [ ] Logged in to GitHub
- [ ] Ready to create repository

### Phase 2: Create Repository (2 minutes)

**Option A: Using GitHub Web Interface**

- [ ] Go to github.com/new
- [ ] Repository name: `mubra-chemistry`
- [ ] Description: "Premium A/L Chemistry AI Tutor"
- [ ] Public (important for GitHub Pages)
- [ ] Click "Create repository"
- [ ] You're on the new repo page

**Option B: Using Git CLI**

```bash
- [ ] Git installed on computer
- [ ] Navigate to mubra-chemistry folder
- [ ] Run: git init
- [ ] Run: git add .
- [ ] Run: git commit -m "Initial commit: Mubra AI"
- [ ] Create repo on GitHub
- [ ] Run: git remote add origin [your repo URL]
- [ ] Run: git push -u origin main
```

### Phase 3: Upload Files (3 minutes)

**Option A: Web Interface**

- [ ] On repo page, click "uploading an existing file"
- [ ] Drag and drop files:
  - [ ] mubra-chemistry-app.html
  - [ ] README.md
  - [ ] QUICKSTART.md
  - [ ] DESIGN-SPECIFICATIONS.md
- [ ] Click "Commit changes"
- [ ] Files appear in repository

**Option B: Git Command**

```bash
- [ ] Files already committed (see above)
- [ ] Push to GitHub complete
```

### Phase 4: Enable GitHub Pages (3 minutes)

- [ ] Go to repository Settings tab
- [ ] Scroll down to "Pages" section
- [ ] Source: "Deploy from a branch"
- [ ] Branch: "main"
- [ ] Folder: "/(root)"
- [ ] Click "Save"
- [ ] Yellow/blue alert appears with your URL
- [ ] Your app is being deployed!

**URL Format:**
```
https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/mubra-chemistry/mubra-chemistry-app.html
```

Or if renamed to index.html:
```
https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/mubra-chemistry/
```

### Phase 5: Wait for Deployment (1-2 minutes)

- [ ] Refresh repository page
- [ ] Green checkmark appears next to commit
- [ ] Status shows "Deployed"
- [ ] Visit your app URL in browser
- [ ] App loads successfully
- [ ] All features work

